An operator shall ensure that information relevant to the flight is preserved on the ground for the duration of each flight or series of flights. This includes:  (select 5)
1 - appropriate meteorological information; 
2 - a copy of the operational flight plan and, if required; 
3 - copies of the relevant parts of the aircraft technical log; 
4 - route specific NOTAM documentation if specifically edited by the operator;
5 - mass and balance documentation if required; 
6 - special loads notification; 
7 - copies of the present performances and limitations with completed charts.

Which documents are carried on a public transport flight?

1.  Certificate of Airworthiness;
2.  Certificate of Registration;
3.  Noise Certificate (if applicable);
4.  Air Operators Certificate;
5.  Aircraft Radio Licence;
6.  Third Party Liability Insurance Certificates;
7.  Valid Flight Crew Licence with appropriate ratings for each flight crew member for the purpose of the flight.

Which statements are correct?
An operator shall ensure that information relevant to the flight is preserved on the ground for the duration of each flight or series of flights. This includes...

- appropriate meteorological information;

- a copy of the operational flight plan and, if required, the mass and balance documentation;

- copies of the relevant parts of the aircraft technical log;

- route specific NOTAM documentation if specifically edited by the operator;

- special loads notification;

- copies of the present performances and limitations with completed charts.</li>
